==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tanager
<hw>Tan"a*ger</hw> <pr>(t⟦acr⟧n"⟦adot⟧*j⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL. <ets>tanagra</ets>, probably fr. Brazilian
<ets>tangara</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of bright-colored singing birds belonging to <gen>Tanagra</gen>,
<gen>Piranga</gen>, and allied genera. The scarlet tanager (<spn>Piranga
erythromelas</spn>) and the summer redbird (<spn>Piranga rubra</spn>)
are common species of the United States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tanagrine</ent>⟦br⟧
